WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.007 --> 00:00:09.050
- Everett!
- Everett. are you in there?

2
00:00:09.134 --> 00:00:11.261
Everett!

3
00:00:11.761 --> 00:00:13.888
Step back.
I'm gonna kick the door down.

4
00:00:15.557 --> 00:00:17.559
- Oh no.
- Oh my God! Everett!

5
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:19.519
Everett. wake up!

6
00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:20.979
Everett.

7
00:00:21.062 --> 00:00:23.481
Dad!

8
00:00:24.232 --> 00:00:26.943
- There's no pulse. I'm starting CPR.
- Yeah. I can help.

9
00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:34.909
How's he doing?

10
00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:36.869
Nothing yet.

11
00:00:39.789 --> 00:00:41.541
Okay. Let's get his shirt up.

12
00:00:43.543 --> 00:00:45.837
Now...

13
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.213
Okay.

14
00:00:47.964 --> 00:00:48.798
Yeah.

15
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:51.134
- Rhythm check.
<i>- Analyzing now.</i>

16
00:00:51.217 --> 00:00:53.553
- In V-tach with a shockable rhythm.
- Okay.

17
00:00:53.636 --> 00:00:55.180
I'm charging to 150 joules.

18
00:00:57.766 --> 00:01:00.018
- Okay. clear.
<i>- Stand clear.</i>

19
00:01:00.101 --> 00:01:02.812
Three. two. one.

20
00:01:04.022 --> 00:01:05.690
<i>Check for pulse.</i>

21
00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:07.525
It didn't work! It didn't work!

22
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:10.445
Still in V-tach.
I'm going again. Charging to 200.

23
00:01:11.571 --> 00:01:12.822
I'm clear. Clear.

24
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:15.325
<i>- Stand clear.</i>
- Three. two. one.

25
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:18.745
<i>Check for pulse.</i>

26
00:01:20.455 --> 00:01:22.582
He has a pulse. It's faint.

27
00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:24.542
Yep. Yeah.

28
00:01:25.043 --> 00:01:26.252
- Yeah.
- He's back.

29
00:01:27.712 --> 00:01:28.797
Yeah.

30
00:01:49.776 --> 00:01:52.862
We only have room for one person
to travel alongside the patient.

31
00:01:52.946 --> 00:01:54.197
You go.

32
00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:56.032
Okay. Okay.

33
00:01:58.493 --> 00:01:59.536
I love you.

34
00:02:03.748 --> 00:02:04.916
I love you too.

35
00:02:05.834 --> 00:02:07.252
He's gonna be okay.

36
00:02:08.503 --> 00:02:10.421
- Okay.
- We'll get there as fast as we can.

37
00:02:10.505 --> 00:02:11.714
Okay.

38
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:18.596
All right. ready for takeoff.

39
00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:13.902
- Hey.
- Hey.

40
00:03:14.527 --> 00:03:15.862
You okay?

41
00:03:17.947 --> 00:03:18.947
I'm all right.

42
00:03:20.617 --> 00:03:22.827
- Thank you for coming.
- Of course!

43
00:03:22.911 --> 00:03:23.912
How... How is he?

44
00:03:25.246 --> 00:03:28.291
It was... It was a heart attack.
so they're putting in a stent now.

45
00:03:28.374 --> 00:03:31.461
Well. don't forget. Hope pulled through
her heart attack just fine.

46
00:03:31.544 --> 00:03:33.087
and she's healthier than ever now.

47
00:03:33.171 --> 00:03:36.591
Thanks to that awful diet
and exercise plan you made for me.

48
00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:42.096
I'm so sorry this is happening
on your wedding day.

49
00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:45.433
Well. we'll figure everything out
once Everett's in the clear.

50
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:50.104
It might not be today. but I am gonna
marry you. come hell or high water.

51
00:03:51.731 --> 00:03:54.150
Yeah. well. with the year we've had.

52
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:56.402
we might have to be prepared for both.

53
00:03:56.486 --> 00:03:57.612
Oh come on.

54
00:03:57.695 --> 00:04:00.531
Okay. I'm gonna get us
something for breakfast.

55
00:04:00.615 --> 00:04:03.326
Worrying on an empty stomach
can give you an ulcer.

56
00:04:03.409 --> 00:04:04.869
Bacon grease goes a long way.

57
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:06.246
- Mmm!
- Ah-ah-ah!

58
00:04:06.329 --> 00:04:08.539
Or I could find something on my diet plan.

59
00:04:08.623 --> 00:04:10.708
because we don't need
another heart attack today.

60
00:04:10.792 --> 00:04:12.919
- No.
- I'll come with you. We're not on a diet.

61
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:15.088
- Bacon sounds good. right? Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

62
00:04:15.171 --> 00:04:16.547
- I'll see you in a bit.
- Thanks.

63
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:19.634
Ugh.

64
00:04:20.134 --> 00:04:21.427
Yeah.

65
00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:27.934
Mmm. Thank you. Thank you for your help.

66
00:04:28.518 --> 00:04:30.311
Yeah. I was just doing my job.

67
00:04:30.979 --> 00:04:33.856
Now he's doing his. Fighting for his life.

68
00:04:35.608 --> 00:04:36.985
Yeah. I hope so.

69
00:04:37.568 --> 00:04:38.653
I know so.

70
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.364
How do you know?

71
00:04:44.575 --> 00:04:48.871
That rift between
me and your father started when I

72
00:04:50.081 --> 00:04:54.085
rushed to save his life
from a bad car accident.

73
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:56.713
And all these years I thought.

74
00:04:56.796 --> 00:05:00.174
"Oh. he was just out
on a drunken joyride."

75
00:05:01.342 --> 00:05:02.427
but he was not.

76
00:05:04.137 --> 00:05:06.931
When we talked. he told me that

77
00:05:08.182 --> 00:05:09.559
he was devastated

78
00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:14.522
by losing your mother
and the chance to get to know you.

79
00:05:14.605 --> 00:05:16.899
and he felt like
he had nothing to live for.

80
00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:19.193
so he made no plans
to come home that night.

81
00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:20.737
Oh my God.

82
00:05:21.529 --> 00:05:25.074
But he is not that man anymore. Mel.

83
00:05:25.867 --> 00:05:29.662
And I can see having you
back in his life has changed him.

84
00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:35.293
For the first time in a long time.
Everett Reid

85
00:05:36.252 --> 00:05:38.338
has something to live for.

86
00:05:40.381 --> 00:05:43.009
And someone to fight for.

87
00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:45.428
And he will.

88
00:05:47.555 --> 00:05:49.182
- I hope so.
- Yeah.

89
00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:52.352
He will.

90
00:06:10.453 --> 00:06:12.330
I'm not sure you should drink that.

91
00:06:13.164 --> 00:06:16.459
Damn robot barista. I hate these machines.

92
00:06:17.251 --> 00:06:18.503
Well. it's not so bad.

93
00:06:18.586 --> 00:06:21.626
It's not like you can kick a real barista
every time he messes up your order.

94
00:06:21.672 --> 00:06:23.216
Not again. I can't.

95
00:06:24.258 --> 00:06:27.887
Hey. I just wanted to say I am so sorry
about the wedding too.

96
00:06:27.970 --> 00:06:31.641
No. no. I know that you put your heart
and soul into making today special.

97
00:06:31.724 --> 00:06:32.934
so thank you.

98
00:06:33.017 --> 00:06:35.978
Don't apologize.
It will happen when it's meant to.

99
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:40.316
Now. Charlie may complain
if it's not today.

100
00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:42.402
He was very excited for his flyover.

101
00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:44.612
- You were doing a flyover?
- We were.

102
00:06:44.695 --> 00:06:46.280
- Hope McCrea.
- Oh...

103
00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:49.826
I just wanted to give you two
the fanfare you deserve.

104
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:51.410
Right.

105
00:06:52.787 --> 00:06:55.415
You've come so far
from the guy I first met. Jack.

106
00:06:56.165 --> 00:06:59.794
That brooding vet
with a dream and a drinking problem.

107
00:07:01.337 --> 00:07:04.674
In hindsight. I probably shouldn't
have helped you open a bar.

108
00:07:06.467 --> 00:07:07.802
Well. you know what?

109
00:07:07.885 --> 00:07:10.555
If you hadn't. I never would have met Mel.

110
00:07:10.638 --> 00:07:13.474
so I am very. very glad that you did.

111
00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:17.061
He is out. He's okay.

112
00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:19.355
Oh. thank heavens!

113
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:21.649
- Phew.
- Okay.

114
00:07:22.358 --> 00:07:24.402
Okay!

115
00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:30.116
It's a very comfortable bed.
Don't you think so?

116
00:07:30.199 --> 00:07:32.410
All right. Uh...

117
00:07:34.162 --> 00:07:35.872
Uh. Jack says that Everett's okay.

118
00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:38.716
He's not sure about the wedding yet.
but they're gonna keep us posted.

119
00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:40.710
Well. let's keep our fingers crossed.

120
00:07:41.210 --> 00:07:44.547
Okay. Good news. Um. orange juice. coffee?

121
00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:47.842
Mmm. both. Champagne in the former.
Baileys in the latter.

122
00:07:47.925 --> 00:07:50.511
Slow down. We can't have a repeat
of Mary's wedding. dear.

123
00:07:50.595 --> 00:07:52.096
- That was Donna.
- Oop!

124
00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:54.891
How lucky am I to have more than one
daughter that could apply to?

125
00:07:55.892 --> 00:08:01.105
Well. I'm excited to meet Mary and Donna.
whether the wedding happens or not.

126
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:04.233
Yeah. and I'm excited to hear what they
think about you two back together.

127
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:06.194
Well. we haven't exactly
talked about that yet.

128
00:08:06.277 --> 00:08:08.237
We are taking it slow.

129
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.322
Mm-hmm.

130
00:08:09.405 --> 00:08:11.991
- Didn't seem like that last night.
- No.

131
00:08:12.074 --> 00:08:13.326
No. it did not.

132
00:08:13.409 --> 00:08:15.036
Okay.

133
00:08:16.078 --> 00:08:18.331
What happened here? Like. what about Javi?

134
00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:22.793
He knows we're giving this a try.
He's supportive. We ended amicably.

135
00:08:22.877 --> 00:08:27.089
But why? 'Cause I thought you two
said you weren't good for each other.

136
00:08:27.173 --> 00:08:30.885
We have things to work on.
but I'm making efforts for your mother.

137
00:08:30.968 --> 00:08:33.054
And I've realized no one is perfect.

138
00:08:33.137 --> 00:08:34.764
Except for Mike here.

139
00:08:34.847 --> 00:08:37.099
You are setting me up for failure. Amelia.

140
00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:40.937
But. seriously.
your father is my soulmate.

141
00:08:41.020 --> 00:08:42.146
Always has been.

142
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:45.024
We may not be perfect on paper. but...

143
00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:50.238
our hearts are connected in ways that.
well. I can't begin to explain.

144
00:08:51.572 --> 00:08:54.492
And since he's doing his best
to be a better man for me.

145
00:08:55.743 --> 00:08:57.954
I feel I owe him a fighting chance.

146
00:08:58.037 --> 00:09:01.832
So... I'm staying open to the possibility.

147
00:09:05.002 --> 00:09:08.381
<i>Cleanup. room 411.
411. cleanup.</i>

148
00:09:25.439 --> 00:09:26.691
Well.

149
00:09:28.109 --> 00:09:29.151
Hey.

150
00:09:29.777 --> 00:09:30.820
Hey. Dad.

151
00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:33.363
"Dad."

152
00:09:35.074 --> 00:09:38.619
Never thought
anyone would call me Dad.

153
00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:41.080
But. I guess if...

154
00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:46.002
...if anyone would. it would be you.

155
00:09:46.627 --> 00:09:48.504
Because I am your dad.

156
00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:53.259
You're loopy from the anesthesia.

157
00:09:53.342 --> 00:09:56.095
Well. that explains a few things.

158
00:09:57.221 --> 00:09:58.764
I saw... I saw your mother...

159
00:10:01.183 --> 00:10:03.102
when I was out. I mean...

160
00:10:05.563 --> 00:10:08.899
I guess it could have been the drugs
or it could have been a dream.

161
00:10:09.442 --> 00:10:13.070
I've had lots of...
Lots of dreams about your mother.

162
00:10:13.821 --> 00:10:14.821
This was...

163
00:10:17.116 --> 00:10:18.367
This was different.

164
00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:21.871
It was...

165
00:10:21.954 --> 00:10:23.331
It was her.

166
00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:27.043
I told her I wanted to stay with her.

167
00:10:30.046 --> 00:10:32.965
But she said.
"There's no way my little girl

168
00:10:34.216 --> 00:10:36.886
is going to lose her father
on her wedding day."

169
00:10:40.806 --> 00:10:44.226
We're... I think we're going to post...
postpone the wedding.

170
00:10:47.104 --> 00:10:49.523
So I came back from the dead for nothing?

171
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:52.026
That's not funny.

172
00:10:55.279 --> 00:10:56.530
No. Mel.

173
00:10:58.157 --> 00:10:59.408
You can't postpone.

174
00:10:59.992 --> 00:11:01.869
Not on my... Not on my account.

175
00:11:04.413 --> 00:11:07.166
Listen. this wedding isn't about me.

176
00:11:08.459 --> 00:11:11.504
Or your friends. or this town.

177
00:11:13.255 --> 00:11:14.715
It's about you and Jack.

178
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:16.509
Always has been.

179
00:11:17.259 --> 00:11:19.345
Nothing's more important than that.

180
00:11:19.428 --> 00:11:23.849
Whether I'm there in person or not.
it doesn't matter.

181
00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:28.479
I'll be right by your side.

182
00:11:29.271 --> 00:11:30.523
So will your mother.

183
00:11:31.649 --> 00:11:33.651
Just like she's been this whole time.

184
00:11:35.194 --> 00:11:36.194
Right?

185
00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:37.571
Yeah.

186
00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:43.035
- Sorry.
- Hey.

187
00:11:48.332 --> 00:11:50.376
So the wedding's back on.

188
00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:52.503
Okay.

189
00:11:52.586 --> 00:11:53.963
But what about Everett?

190
00:11:54.046 --> 00:11:56.382
He insisted. This is what he wants.

191
00:11:57.007 --> 00:11:58.759
Okay. What about what you want?

192
00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:01.178
I know how much it meant to you
to have him there.

193
00:12:01.262 --> 00:12:05.433
I know. It does. But I don't want to wait
another minute to marry you. so...

194
00:12:05.516 --> 00:12:09.770
Well. you have to wait another 473.

195
00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:11.480
But who's counting?

196
00:12:11.564 --> 00:12:13.691
- Okay. you go home and get ready.
- Yes.

197
00:12:13.774 --> 00:12:16.026
And you don't forget
Roland is coming to pick up Sugar.

198
00:12:16.110 --> 00:12:18.904
- Yep.
- And you. kiss me already.

199
00:12:18.988 --> 00:12:20.740
- Yeah.
- Kiss her.

200
00:12:20.823 --> 00:12:23.033
- See you guys. Yep. Bye.
- See you both at the barn.

201
00:12:23.117 --> 00:12:24.368
- Bye.
- Okay.

202
00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:31.292
<i>Hey.</i>

203
00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:34.128
We are going to the chapel.
and we're gonna get married.

204
00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:37.882
I repeat. we are going to the chapel.
and we're gonna get married.

205
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:40.009
Copy that.

206
00:12:40.092 --> 00:12:44.388
Ladies and gentlemen. we are going
to the chapel of love! The wedding is on!

207
00:12:48.017 --> 00:12:49.310
Put me on speaker.

208
00:12:50.936 --> 00:12:54.732
<i>Hey. folks. I'll be there to handle
the big stuff. but while I'm on the road.</i>

209
00:12:54.815 --> 00:12:56.484
<i>I officially transfer</i>

210
00:12:56.567 --> 00:13:00.237
<i>the matrimonial power
vested in me by the State of California</i>

211
00:13:00.321 --> 00:13:02.698
<i>and the voters of Virgin River to you.</i>

212
00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:04.241
Can you handle it?

213
00:13:04.950 --> 00:13:07.620
Yes. Mayor. you can count on us.

214
00:13:08.287 --> 00:13:10.206
Okay. See you. Bye.

215
00:13:15.669 --> 00:13:17.129
Is that Dr. Hayes?

216
00:13:17.213 --> 00:13:18.339
Oh. in the flesh.

217
00:13:18.422 --> 00:13:20.525
You should give that man
a piece of your mind. Vernon.

218
00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:22.468
No. He already knows how I feel.

219
00:13:22.551 --> 00:13:24.512
- Still.
- Dr. Mullins?

220
00:13:24.595 --> 00:13:26.931
- Yes.
- Mr. Reid is asking for you.

221
00:13:27.014 --> 00:13:28.265
Saved by Everett Reid.

222
00:13:28.349 --> 00:13:30.267
Who would have thought?

223
00:13:30.768 --> 00:13:32.436
- I'll wait for you here.
- Yeah.

224
00:13:43.197 --> 00:13:44.573
Jo Ellen. alert the phone tree

225
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:47.576
that everyone dropping off food
down at the barn can start to load in.

226
00:13:47.660 --> 00:13:49.829
- Nick. keep feeding that smoker.
- You got it.

227
00:13:49.912 --> 00:13:52.122
Hannah. bar setup. deck left.

228
00:13:52.206 --> 00:13:56.168
Aunt Connie. secure a spot for the bakery
truck to park for the dessert bar.

229
00:13:56.252 --> 00:13:58.963
And. Lydie. confirm that
the tablescapes are perfect.

230
00:13:59.046 --> 00:14:00.881
and the name cards
are placed appropriately.

231
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:04.844
Denny. you and I will supervise
band loading and site setup.

232
00:14:04.927 --> 00:14:07.388
and then we will decorate
the "just married" car.

233
00:14:08.138 --> 00:14:10.778
You run a tight ship. That little girl's
in for a world of trouble.

234
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.059
Not if she listens. she's not.

235
00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:20.484
Hey. let me... Let me help you with that.

236
00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:21.402
Thanks. man.

237
00:14:21.485 --> 00:14:25.906
Yeah. this hospital Jell-O
is sealed like a fortress. isn't it?

238
00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:28.784
Pudding is damn near impossible.

239
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:31.120
Here. this is the way.

240
00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:34.748
Oh!

241
00:14:39.795 --> 00:14:44.341
Now. the nurse said that. uh. there was
something you want to talk about.

242
00:14:47.052 --> 00:14:49.179
Well. I was hoping
you could do me a favor.

243
00:14:50.514 --> 00:14:52.641
Would you walk Mel down the aisle for me?

244
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:57.563
I know you were planning to do it before.

245
00:15:00.524 --> 00:15:01.817
It would be my honor.

246
00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:03.861
Thank you.

247
00:15:06.196 --> 00:15:08.198
And would you give her something for me?

248
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:12.620
I finished the song she wanted me to sing
at the wedding. and...

249
00:15:14.538 --> 00:15:16.999
Well. I'd like her to have the lyrics
as a wedding present.

250
00:15:17.499 --> 00:15:19.835
They're in a notebook back at my house.

251
00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:23.672
Uh...

252
00:15:25.341 --> 00:15:27.092
Yeah. tell you what. I...

253
00:15:28.177 --> 00:15:29.970
I would be glad to help you.

254
00:15:31.555 --> 00:15:33.057
on one condition.

255
00:15:38.646 --> 00:15:41.273
Excuse me. Dr. Hayes.

256
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:43.150
Yes. can I help you?

257
00:15:43.233 --> 00:15:46.320
Hope McCrea. Vernon Mullins' wife
and the Mayor of Virgin River.

258
00:15:46.403 --> 00:15:49.531
I know you're coming after
Vernon's medical license.

259
00:15:49.615 --> 00:15:52.201
and I've got a bone
to pick with you about that.

260
00:15:53.035 --> 00:15:55.412
- As his wife or the mayor?
- Both.

261
00:15:55.913 --> 00:15:59.875
Look. you need to understand
that my husband's medical practice

262
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:01.835
is the cornerstone of our town.

263
00:16:01.919 --> 00:16:04.672
Sure. Vernon's methods can be unorthodox.

264
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:07.383
and his moods
are frequently unpleasant. but...

265
00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:09.593
practically everyone in Virgin River

266
00:16:09.677 --> 00:16:12.137
owes my husband their lives
in one way or another.

267
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:15.516
Don't punish him for the ability
to think outside the box.

268
00:16:15.599 --> 00:16:21.021
He saved a life while training
a college student in the process.

269
00:16:21.105 --> 00:16:22.606
You mean a medical student.

270
00:16:23.107 --> 00:16:24.566
In a couple years. yes.

271
00:16:25.359 --> 00:16:26.986
I'm sorry. are you telling me

272
00:16:27.069 --> 00:16:29.822
that Dr. Mullins' intern
is an undergraduate college student?

273
00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:33.450
I think you're missing my point.

274
00:16:33.534 --> 00:16:35.703
No. I think I got your point
loud and clear.

275
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:37.496
I knew your husband had been foolish.

276
00:16:37.579 --> 00:16:39.957
but now I know
he could've been downright negligent.

277
00:16:42.126 --> 00:16:43.293
Oh...

278
00:16:46.839 --> 00:16:49.842
Can I get a double latte
with coconut milk for the bride?

279
00:16:49.925 --> 00:16:51.176
Absolutely.

280
00:16:52.761 --> 00:16:55.264
Brie! Hey. how are you?

281
00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:57.933
Hey. I'm good. How are you?

282
00:16:58.017 --> 00:16:59.184
Fine.

283
00:16:59.268 --> 00:17:00.728
Oh!

284
00:17:01.812 --> 00:17:03.605
Why "oh"?

285
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:07.776
I don't know. I guess I just
figured the breakup might have been hard

286
00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:09.778
considering how much
was on the line for you.

287
00:17:09.862 --> 00:17:12.906
- Did Brady talk to you about it?
- About conning him?

288
00:17:13.782 --> 00:17:15.242
I actually told him.

289
00:17:15.743 --> 00:17:19.079
Yeah. 'cause I...
I saw you at the prison with Jimmy.

290
00:17:20.039 --> 00:17:23.208
And then. you know. it didn't take Brady
long to put the pieces together.

291
00:17:23.292 --> 00:17:24.918
You shouldn't have underestimated him.

292
00:17:25.002 --> 00:17:27.212
I don't think I'm the one
who underestimated him.

293
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:31.800
I don't know who you think you are. Lark.

294
00:17:32.760 --> 00:17:34.595
but now that you're not with Brady.

295
00:17:34.678 --> 00:17:37.306
I don't have to pretend to like you. so...

296
00:17:37.389 --> 00:17:38.849
Thank you so much.

297
00:17:52.988 --> 00:17:56.283
Dr. Hayek. what brings you
to the clinic this morning?

298
00:17:56.366 --> 00:17:59.286
Well. you said you were getting
the results from your biopsy. so...

299
00:17:59.369 --> 00:18:00.704
Yeah! Um...

300
00:18:01.205 --> 00:18:03.665
My tumor is HER2-positive.

301
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:07.086
Okay. so that means they're gonna do
chemo first. right. before surgery?

302
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:09.254
See if they can try
and shrink the tumor. Yeah.

303
00:18:09.338 --> 00:18:13.675
Yeah. and then they'll decide if I'm
to have a lumpectomy or a full mastectomy.

304
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:17.971
Like I'm playing this game
of <i>Sophie's Chest.</i>

305
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:22.142
You're still funny.

306
00:18:22.226 --> 00:18:25.979
Mmm! Yeah. well. you just wait
until I start wearing the clown wig.

307
00:18:26.063 --> 00:18:28.732
Hey. no. no.
Hair loss is not a given these days.

308
00:18:30.025 --> 00:18:34.488
But either way. I'm not going to have
the carefree spring I was expecting.

309
00:18:34.571 --> 00:18:36.156
Hey. it might not be that bad.

310
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:38.158
Everybody reacts differently to chemo.

311
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:40.119
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

312
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:43.747
And how do people
you've just started dating react to it?

313
00:18:45.332 --> 00:18:46.542
You're dating someone.

314
00:18:47.209 --> 00:18:48.127
Walt Booth.

315
00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:50.712
- Mmm.
- I mean. our relationship is so new. it's...

316
00:18:50.796 --> 00:18:52.840
I don't even know if I can call it that.

317
00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:55.092
But I do know I really...

318
00:18:55.175 --> 00:18:58.637
Mmm. I really like him.
I don't want to scare him away.

319
00:19:00.055 --> 00:19:02.266
- Yeah.
- I mean. the last guy I was dating...

320
00:19:02.349 --> 00:19:05.060
Oof! He just left
because I didn't wanna have kids.

321
00:19:05.144 --> 00:19:06.436
Okay...

322
00:19:07.771 --> 00:19:09.481
You said you understood.

323
00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:12.317
Oh. I know I did. and I meant it.

324
00:19:13.193 --> 00:19:14.403
Doesn't mean it didn't hurt.

325
00:19:17.322 --> 00:19:18.322
Yeah.

326
00:19:19.491 --> 00:19:23.370
You can understand something
and still have it break your heart.

327
00:19:25.622 --> 00:19:26.622
Yeah.

328
00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:38.552
Well...

329
00:19:38.635 --> 00:19:42.055
I know we weren't supposed to
see each other on our wedding day. but...

330
00:19:44.141 --> 00:19:45.893
I'm really glad I was with you.

331
00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:47.811
Yeah. me too.

332
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:51.398
I don't think I could have handled it
this morning if you weren't there.

333
00:19:51.481 --> 00:19:52.481
Mmm.

334
00:20:00.657 --> 00:20:04.453
The thought of losing my dad
when I just found him was really scary.

335
00:20:05.495 --> 00:20:06.496
I know.

336
00:20:07.873 --> 00:20:11.293
Hey. I'm serious.
If you don't want to do this today...

337
00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:14.546
No. no. I do. I do. I just. um...

338
00:20:14.630 --> 00:20:17.799
Hey! Let's go. We gotta get
this woman into hair and makeup.

339
00:20:17.883 --> 00:20:18.967
Oh.

340
00:20:20.135 --> 00:20:22.137
You know. she could have been
a Marine captain too.

341
00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:23.847
Oh. no doubt.

342
00:20:23.931 --> 00:20:26.141
- Okay. cadet. hop to it.
- Okay.

343
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:28.727
Unless you want to finish that thought?

344
00:20:30.187 --> 00:20:31.187
Oh.

345
00:20:31.647 --> 00:20:35.234
You know. I don't even...
I don't even know what I was going to say.

346
00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:38.695
I. uh. I love you.
and that's all that matters.

347
00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:40.656
and. um. I will see you at the altar.

348
00:20:42.032 --> 00:20:43.033
You will.

349
00:20:56.046 --> 00:20:57.965
- Okay.
- Thank you.

350
00:20:58.048 --> 00:21:00.109
- You... And that is...
- This is me. that's you.

351
00:21:00.133 --> 00:21:01.718
- Hi.
- Mel.

352
00:21:01.802 --> 00:21:03.470
- Hi.
- Hi.

353
00:21:05.347 --> 00:21:07.057
- Coffee.
- Oh. thank you.

354
00:21:07.140 --> 00:21:09.559
So glad Everett's okay.

355
00:21:09.643 --> 00:21:10.643
I know.

356
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:14.022
We were so worried.
But now there's nothing to worry about.

357
00:21:15.732 --> 00:21:19.069
Okay. What's...
What's going on?

358
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.531
Where's Charmaine?

359
00:21:23.073 --> 00:21:25.575
I called her. and she didn't answer.

360
00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:28.870
Okay. um...

361
00:21:28.954 --> 00:21:31.498
Well. maybe I missed a text
from her or something.

362
00:21:32.624 --> 00:21:36.628
Yeah. she said. um. "Something came up
that I had to deal with."

363
00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:38.422
Oh. could it be the twins?

364
00:21:38.505 --> 00:21:41.216
Or maybe she's having second thoughts
about seeing Jack get married.

365
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:44.803
Either way. we don't have
anyone to do your hair.

366
00:21:44.886 --> 00:21:46.596
- Yet!
- Yeah.

367
00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.640
- But we're gonna find someone!
- Yes.

368
00:21:49.141 --> 00:21:51.518
- Aw. Hope.
- I was trying to help!

369
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:55.063
But you didn't help.
What you did is the opposite of help.

370
00:21:55.147 --> 00:21:58.525
Yes. but I didn't know
that's what I was doing at the time.

371
00:21:58.608 --> 00:22:00.360
Well. you... you should have known better.

372
00:22:00.986 --> 00:22:02.571
Why would I know better?

373
00:22:03.071 --> 00:22:06.199
Solving your problems behind your back
usually works out fine for you.

374
00:22:06.283 --> 00:22:08.785
Yeah. well. this time
it may cost me everything.

375
00:22:08.869 --> 00:22:11.330
Well. not everything.

376
00:22:11.955 --> 00:22:13.540
I am not laughing at this.

377
00:22:14.041 --> 00:22:16.585
This is my legacy.
Thirty years of hard work.

378
00:22:17.085 --> 00:22:19.963
And... And I may lose it all
because you don't know when to quit!

379
00:22:20.672 --> 00:22:22.257
You're just too much.

380
00:22:24.176 --> 00:22:27.721
You have two seconds to take that back.
Vernon Mullins!

381
00:22:29.306 --> 00:22:30.306
One...

382
00:22:30.349 --> 00:22:31.349
Two!

383
00:22:36.605 --> 00:22:38.357
That's a beautiful animal.
Jack.

384
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:39.441
He really is.

385
00:22:40.442 --> 00:22:44.112
- You sure you want to get rid of him?
- Oh. come on. I'm not getting rid of him.

386
00:22:44.196 --> 00:22:48.033
I'm finding him a new home with someone
who knows how to take care of horses.

387
00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:50.619
Honestly. it's the best thing for him.

388
00:22:51.536 --> 00:22:53.789
Oh. I'm sure gonna miss him. though.

389
00:22:54.373 --> 00:22:56.458
What do you say. boy? Hmm?

390
00:22:56.541 --> 00:23:01.046
How about we go for one more ride?
Help clear our heads a bit. you know?

391
00:23:01.129 --> 00:23:02.381
Calm our nerves?

392
00:23:02.464 --> 00:23:05.133
Yeah. I don't think you riding a horse
on your wedding day

393
00:23:05.217 --> 00:23:06.551
is the best decision there. Jack.

394
00:23:07.135 --> 00:23:08.220
Thankfully...

395
00:23:09.179 --> 00:23:11.598
it's not your decision to make.

396
00:23:11.681 --> 00:23:13.392
You have plausible deniability.

397
00:23:13.475 --> 00:23:15.894
I'm pretty sure that's not
how plausible deniability works.

398
00:23:15.977 --> 00:23:16.853
See you in a few.

399
00:23:16.937 --> 00:23:17.937
Come on!

400
00:23:19.689 --> 00:23:22.901
Okay. If anything happens to him.
Mel's gonna kill us.

401
00:23:22.984 --> 00:23:25.737
Well. if you can stop him. be my guest.

402
00:23:33.912 --> 00:23:36.331
I... I promise.
we're gonna figure this out.

403
00:23:37.124 --> 00:23:37.999
What?

404
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:39.251
- Your hair.
- Oh. right.

405
00:23:39.334 --> 00:23:43.046
Yeah. Jo Ellen. she's just
working on some options. so it's gonna...

406
00:23:43.130 --> 00:23:44.589
Yeah. Right.

407
00:23:45.549 --> 00:23:49.010
Well. why don't...
Why don't we just have Joey do it? Joey?

408
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:52.055
You did my hair for prom.
and I won prom queen that night.

409
00:23:52.139 --> 00:23:53.890
Uh. no. you did not.

410
00:23:53.974 --> 00:23:58.270
Well. I felt like a prom queen.
all thanks to you.

411
00:23:59.312 --> 00:24:02.149
Come on! Will you do me the honor
of doing my hair. please?

412
00:24:02.232 --> 00:24:03.650
I will.

413
00:24:03.733 --> 00:24:05.819
- Oh!
- Please let that be Charmaine.

414
00:24:05.902 --> 00:24:07.112
Please. please.

415
00:24:11.324 --> 00:24:12.576
- Oh.
- Hello. ladies.

416
00:24:12.659 --> 00:24:14.703
Hi! Not Charmaine.

417
00:24:15.245 --> 00:24:17.247
You're... You're Paul. right?

418
00:24:17.330 --> 00:24:19.666
- The Christmas elf from Santa's village.
- Yeah.

419
00:24:19.749 --> 00:24:22.419
Uh. what... What are you doing here?

420
00:24:22.502 --> 00:24:26.006
Well. as a typical millennial gig worker.

421
00:24:26.089 --> 00:24:28.175
Hope hired me
to be your wedding videographer.

422
00:24:28.884 --> 00:24:31.386
- Oh!
- I'm here to document your big day.

423
00:24:31.470 --> 00:24:34.306
Ah. okay. Well. I would
love for you to film the wedding.

424
00:24:34.389 --> 00:24:37.142
but I don't know
that I need video of me getting ready.

425
00:24:37.225 --> 00:24:39.060
It's all part of the package.

426
00:24:39.144 --> 00:24:42.564
When I edit it together. you're gonna
be glad you have it. I promise.

427
00:24:42.647 --> 00:24:44.232
You won't even notice I'm here.

428
00:24:45.233 --> 00:24:47.652
Okay. All right. Come on in. Come on in.

429
00:24:47.736 --> 00:24:53.492
Actually. if you could open the door again
and then non-verbally invite me in.

430
00:24:53.575 --> 00:24:55.869
it'd make for a really cool entrance shot.

431
00:24:55.952 --> 00:24:58.955
Oh no. I absolutely can't do that.
I'm sorry.

432
00:24:59.039 --> 00:25:00.665
Fair.

433
00:25:10.967 --> 00:25:15.305
<i>♪ I've been sitting around
For way too long ♪</i>

434
00:25:15.388 --> 00:25:20.310
<i>♪ And the world is looking like
It's getting smaller by the minute ♪</i>

435
00:25:20.393 --> 00:25:26.691
<i>♪ I am bound up in chains
And I just have to say ♪</i>

436
00:25:26.775 --> 00:25:32.030
<i>♪ Let me run
Like the horses on the range ♪</i>

437
00:25:32.113 --> 00:25:36.451
<i>♪ And I promise you
I'll never ever complain ♪</i>

438
00:25:39.079 --> 00:25:40.455
You must be Jack.

439
00:25:41.248 --> 00:25:43.833
Yeah. and you must be the devil incarnate.

440
00:25:44.543 --> 00:25:47.087
I see my reputation precedes me.

441
00:25:47.712 --> 00:25:49.381
You look mighty at home up there.

442
00:25:49.464 --> 00:25:52.175
Ah. it's all Sugar. He makes it easy.

443
00:25:52.259 --> 00:25:55.095
Ah. well. if he'll let you
ride him like that.

444
00:25:55.178 --> 00:25:57.472
he's gonna make a great little show pony.

445
00:25:59.224 --> 00:26:00.934
What do you mean "show pony"?

446
00:26:01.017 --> 00:26:03.395
Well. we host birthday parties
out at the ranch.

447
00:26:03.478 --> 00:26:06.690
Kids take turns riding the horses
around the paddock. It's cute.

448
00:26:07.774 --> 00:26:11.444
Yeah. well. Hope and I just...
nursed this horse back to health.

449
00:26:11.528 --> 00:26:13.530
I thought he was getting
a real second chance.

450
00:26:13.613 --> 00:26:16.616
Well. there are worse fates
for an old horse.

451
00:26:18.785 --> 00:26:20.370
Yeah. I suppose there are.

452
00:26:21.955 --> 00:26:23.957
I suppose there's better ones too.

453
00:26:30.463 --> 00:26:33.633
- Oh my God. Mel.
- You look stunning.

454
00:26:33.717 --> 00:26:35.010
Nice job.

455
00:26:35.093 --> 00:26:37.220
Thank you. I've still got it.

456
00:26:40.181 --> 00:26:41.600
You look like Mom.

457
00:26:43.518 --> 00:26:46.146
That's the best compliment ever.
Thank you. honey.

458
00:26:51.192 --> 00:26:53.528
You know. I actually have
something for you.

459
00:26:54.446 --> 00:26:56.281
- Yeah?
- Something old.

460
00:27:00.535 --> 00:27:01.535
Okay.

461
00:27:07.667 --> 00:27:09.294
They're Dad's cuff links.

462
00:27:10.629 --> 00:27:14.424
I thought maybe you could
wrap them around your bouquet.

463
00:27:16.343 --> 00:27:19.471
Mom got them for Dad
when he got his first job in LA.

464
00:27:20.347 --> 00:27:25.352
They are moonstone.
which help to embrace new beginnings.

465
00:27:28.772 --> 00:27:31.941
Honey. I know Everett
was supposed to be here to keep Mom close.

466
00:27:33.360 --> 00:27:35.945
But... maybe these will work.

467
00:27:36.696 --> 00:27:39.616
And... keep our dad close too.

468
00:27:42.410 --> 00:27:45.914
I love that idea. Thank you. Thank you.

469
00:27:45.997 --> 00:27:47.957
- I love you.
- Love you too.

470
00:27:52.754 --> 00:27:53.755
Come here.

471
00:27:57.258 --> 00:27:58.677
Mmm. aww...

472
00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:00.929
You are beautiful.

473
00:28:02.764 --> 00:28:03.765
Aw.

474
00:28:04.766 --> 00:28:07.185
- I can do it. I got time.
- Okay? Yeah? Perfect.

475
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:09.771
Look who I found.

476
00:28:09.854 --> 00:28:11.856
Joey's sitter
just dropped them off with me.

477
00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:14.943
Hey. I'm Lizzie. Are you little ones
ready for your big jobs?

478
00:28:15.026 --> 00:28:16.569
- I am!
- Me too.

479
00:28:16.653 --> 00:28:19.531
The flower girl goes first. right?
Before the ring bearers?

480
00:28:19.614 --> 00:28:23.159
They're very excited.
They told me it was their first wedding.

481
00:28:23.243 --> 00:28:25.578
Well. believe it or not.
it's my first wedding too.

482
00:28:25.662 --> 00:28:26.705
You're not married?

483
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:28.790
No. I'm not.

484
00:28:28.873 --> 00:28:33.002
That's weird. How did you get pregnant
if you're not married?

485
00:28:34.462 --> 00:28:35.462
Um...

486
00:28:35.505 --> 00:28:41.553
I... I think your parents can explain that
in a decade or so.

487
00:28:41.636 --> 00:28:44.264
Now. who wants lemonade?

488
00:28:44.347 --> 00:28:45.849
- Me.
- I do!

489
00:28:45.932 --> 00:28:48.893
Okay. right this way.

490
00:28:48.977 --> 00:28:51.896
And then we'll practice
walking down the aisle.

491
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:52.980
- Okay.
- Hey.

492
00:28:53.022 --> 00:28:56.484
The "just married" car is done.
What should I do next. boss?

493
00:28:56.568 --> 00:28:57.902
Apparently. you should marry me.

494
00:28:59.446 --> 00:29:01.698
Lizzie? We need you.

495
00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:05.410
Relax. I'm just kidding.

496
00:29:11.040 --> 00:29:15.170
This is all looking great!
Are you feeling good? Oh. did Roland come?

497
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:18.381
Uh. I am. and he did.

498
00:29:18.465 --> 00:29:21.885
I'm sad I didn't get a chance
to say goodbye to Sugar.

499
00:29:21.968 --> 00:29:22.968
Mm-hmm.

500
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:26.139
Actually. you won't have to.
Sugar's not going anywhere.

501
00:29:26.222 --> 00:29:28.433
This is his home as much as it is ours.

502
00:29:28.516 --> 00:29:30.643
Oh. Jack! Oh!

503
00:29:31.644 --> 00:29:33.604
- Can we put him in the wedding?
- Absolutely not.

504
00:29:33.646 --> 00:29:35.899
He's tied up behind the barn
for the evening.

505
00:29:35.982 --> 00:29:37.442
Ah. probably for the best.

506
00:29:37.525 --> 00:29:40.165
I bet Roland was so upset
he had to drive all this way for nothing.

507
00:29:40.236 --> 00:29:43.281
Did he grumble about gas money?
He always grumbled about gas money.

508
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:46.993
Yeah. he did. He told me he spent $100
on diesel to go home empty-handed.

509
00:29:47.076 --> 00:29:48.495
I may have made a new enemy.

510
00:29:48.578 --> 00:29:49.954
You're in good company.

511
00:29:50.038 --> 00:29:52.624
- Okay.
- What made you decide to keep Sugar?

512
00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:55.335
Honestly. I have no idea.

513
00:29:55.877 --> 00:29:56.877
I do.

514
00:29:57.504 --> 00:30:00.548
Classic Jack Sheridan. No man left behind.

515
00:30:01.174 --> 00:30:03.051
Apparently that also applies to horses.

516
00:30:03.134 --> 00:30:06.471
- Ah. come on.
- No. No. it's true.

517
00:30:06.971 --> 00:30:10.725
I mean. look. I know you've struggled
with what happened over there.

518
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:13.019
but what you think is a liability.

519
00:30:13.102 --> 00:30:16.940
that urge you have to believe
in all of us. take care of us all.

520
00:30:17.690 --> 00:30:19.275
it's your greatest asset. brother.

521
00:30:19.359 --> 00:30:20.527
That's why we love you.

522
00:30:21.069 --> 00:30:22.069
Mel included.

523
00:30:25.698 --> 00:30:27.242
Well. thanks. Preach.

524
00:30:27.325 --> 00:30:30.453
Speaking of Mel. we better go get dressed
for this wedding. I'll see you later.

525
00:30:30.537 --> 00:30:31.830
- See ya.
- Yep. Bye.

526
00:30:34.249 --> 00:30:35.500
Nicely put.

527
00:30:36.292 --> 00:30:38.378
I hope your best man speech can top that!

528
00:30:38.878 --> 00:30:41.965
Yeah. so do I. Mike. So do I.

529
00:30:57.939 --> 00:31:00.441
Hi. Look who it is.

530
00:31:01.901 --> 00:31:04.195
Oh my goodness! How are you?

531
00:31:04.279 --> 00:31:05.280
Hi!

532
00:31:08.491 --> 00:31:11.953
Oh. my girls! This is so exciting.

533
00:31:12.036 --> 00:31:14.998
I just love that my kids
are finally in one place again.

534
00:31:15.081 --> 00:31:17.083
And we're here to enjoy it together.
my darling.

535
00:31:17.166 --> 00:31:18.167
Mm-hmm.

536
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:21.129
I bet Donna you'd work it out
and end up back together.

537
00:31:21.212 --> 00:31:23.298
- And now I owe Mary 50 bucks.
- What?

538
00:31:23.381 --> 00:31:26.259
But it was money well spent.
I'm happy for you two.

539
00:31:26.843 --> 00:31:28.261
Thank you for your support.

540
00:31:30.263 --> 00:31:33.057
Come here for a sec! Oh my gosh. hi!

541
00:31:33.141 --> 00:31:35.184
Uh. Walt. this is Cameron.

542
00:31:35.268 --> 00:31:37.896
Cameron. this is Walt.

543
00:31:37.979 --> 00:31:40.940
- It's nice to meet you. sir.
- Pleasure to meet you. Cameron.

544
00:31:41.524 --> 00:31:42.525
Doc!

545
00:31:55.788 --> 00:31:59.751
Hello. Vernon. Is there anything
you'd like to say to me?

546
00:31:59.834 --> 00:32:00.835
Yeah.

547
00:32:02.211 --> 00:32:04.088
I think I'll have some lemonade.

548
00:32:16.267 --> 00:32:17.268
Oh!

549
00:32:27.528 --> 00:32:28.863
This reception is gonna be...

550
00:32:28.947 --> 00:32:31.574
It's a lot. uh.
bigger than I imagined.

551
00:32:32.241 --> 00:32:35.954
I didn't expect you to have this many
ice sculptures at your wedding.

552
00:32:36.037 --> 00:32:38.831
Didn't expect you
to have any ice sculptures.

553
00:32:38.915 --> 00:32:40.833
Well. Hope insisted.

554
00:32:46.005 --> 00:32:51.427
The local artisan offered
to donate them. so how could we say no?

555
00:32:52.178 --> 00:32:53.846
Well. it's gonna be beautiful.

556
00:32:53.930 --> 00:32:57.475
You're gonna be beautiful in this dress.
So let's get you in it. Come on.

557
00:32:57.558 --> 00:32:58.810
Okay. That's great.

558
00:32:58.893 --> 00:32:59.936
Yeah.

559
00:33:00.019 --> 00:33:02.206
- All right? Good. You got it.
- Thank you. Okay.

560
00:33:06.150 --> 00:33:07.819
Okay.

561
00:33:07.902 --> 00:33:09.570
Ah. thank you.

562
00:33:09.654 --> 00:33:10.989
I would like to propose a toast.

563
00:33:11.948 --> 00:33:12.991
Okay.

564
00:33:13.074 --> 00:33:16.244
To sisters old and new.

565
00:33:16.327 --> 00:33:19.205
To some things borrowed
and some things blue.

566
00:33:19.288 --> 00:33:22.041
I'm so happy my brother's marrying you.

567
00:33:22.542 --> 00:33:24.702
- And that I was able to make that rhyme.
- Hey.

568
00:33:25.837 --> 00:33:27.630
No. but really...

569
00:33:30.133 --> 00:33:31.134
Aww.

570
00:33:32.510 --> 00:33:34.178
Thank you for loving my brother.

571
00:33:34.929 --> 00:33:36.681
More than anyone reasonably should.

572
00:33:36.764 --> 00:33:39.392
- I love you.
- Aww! Love you too.

573
00:33:40.393 --> 00:33:42.020
- Thank you.
- Cheers!

574
00:33:42.103 --> 00:33:43.354
Cheers!

575
00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:45.606
Mm-hmm!

576
00:33:46.649 --> 00:33:49.193
And we gotta go. That means you too. Paul.

577
00:33:49.277 --> 00:33:50.361
See you there.

578
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:53.197
- Okay! See you there.
- All right. See you there.

579
00:33:54.615 --> 00:33:57.160
Remember. just act natural.

580
00:33:59.912 --> 00:34:00.912
Right.

581
00:34:03.583 --> 00:34:04.751
- Oy.
- Yeah.

582
00:34:05.460 --> 00:34:06.753
And then there were two.

583
00:34:07.837 --> 00:34:10.048
Yep. as long as I can remember.

584
00:34:14.218 --> 00:34:16.804
Look at you!

585
00:34:17.513 --> 00:34:19.807
You clean up nice. Chief.

586
00:34:19.891 --> 00:34:22.143
Yeah. you look pretty good
yourself there. Chef.

587
00:34:22.226 --> 00:34:24.020
- Thank you.
- How's the speech coming?

588
00:34:24.103 --> 00:34:24.979
Yeah. it's good!

589
00:34:25.063 --> 00:34:28.691
Uh. you know. it was running
about 20 minutes long. so I've...

590
00:34:28.775 --> 00:34:32.945
I've cut out the origin story of...
of. uh. you know. Jack and my friendship.

591
00:34:33.029 --> 00:34:34.489
That part wasn't important. so...

592
00:34:34.572 --> 00:34:37.366
Yeah. good idea. Gotta make 'em laugh.
make 'em cry. let 'em eat cake.

593
00:34:37.450 --> 00:34:42.538
Yeah! Uh. so. anyways. I. um...
I drilled down on my theme.

594
00:34:42.622 --> 00:34:44.916
- Okay. Hmm.
- What do you think of this?

595
00:34:46.667 --> 00:34:47.710
"Marriage..."

596
00:34:47.794 --> 00:34:48.794
Great start.

597
00:34:50.254 --> 00:34:56.511
"It takes grit. passion. and an unwavering
commitment to grow together. not apart."

598
00:34:58.179 --> 00:35:00.348
"Marriage is not for the faint of heart."

599
00:35:00.431 --> 00:35:03.518
"And you two have proven
time and again that your love..."

600
00:35:05.103 --> 00:35:07.939
You're not... You're not buying it.
Is it that bad?

601
00:35:08.022 --> 00:35:09.398
Um. no.

602
00:35:09.482 --> 00:35:12.193
No.
Uh. just save it for the reception. okay?

603
00:35:12.902 --> 00:35:14.445
Wow. you look great.

604
00:35:22.870 --> 00:35:25.706
- We love you. Mel and Jack.
- Happy wedding day!

605
00:35:25.790 --> 00:35:26.624
Mwah!

606
00:35:26.707 --> 00:35:28.084
Happy wedding day!

607
00:35:28.167 --> 00:35:31.671
Do you want to point to Mel and Jack?
Happy wedding day!

608
00:35:31.754 --> 00:35:34.132
- You did it. man. Congratulations.
- Yes. he did.

609
00:35:34.215 --> 00:35:37.176
Hey. hey. hey. They didn't do it yet.
They didn't do it yet.

610
00:35:37.260 --> 00:35:40.888
Yeah. I know. But they're not gonna
see this until after they've done it.

611
00:35:40.972 --> 00:35:42.890
- Oh!
- Whatever. Idiots. Just...

612
00:35:42.974 --> 00:35:44.183
Just say congrats.

613
00:35:44.267 --> 00:35:46.477
- Congratulations.
- I already said congratulations.

614
00:35:46.561 --> 00:35:48.563
- Say it again. man!
- What? Congrats.

615
00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:51.399
Best wedding ever! Best couple ever.

616
00:35:51.482 --> 00:35:54.944
I'm obsessed with you both.
Live long and prosper.

617
00:35:59.574 --> 00:36:01.200
- You made it.
- Hi!

618
00:36:01.284 --> 00:36:03.995
We did. No small feat.

619
00:36:04.078 --> 00:36:07.248
You and Jack definitely chose
to live off the beaten path.

620
00:36:07.331 --> 00:36:08.249
So pretty. though.

621
00:36:08.332 --> 00:36:10.001
I see you've met Mike.

622
00:36:10.084 --> 00:36:12.253
We have. And for such a small town.

623
00:36:12.336 --> 00:36:16.048
you seem to have no trouble
finding shockingly attractive men to date.

624
00:36:16.132 --> 00:36:17.008
Ah.

625
00:36:17.091 --> 00:36:18.968
Try not to mess this one up.

626
00:36:19.051 --> 00:36:21.429
- Uh...
- She didn't mess the last one up.

627
00:36:21.512 --> 00:36:22.847
That was all. um...

628
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:30.313
Brady.

629
00:36:30.813 --> 00:36:32.064
Attention. please!

630
00:36:32.148 --> 00:36:34.025
If everyone would
start to take their seats.

631
00:36:34.108 --> 00:36:35.818
the ceremony will begin in a few minutes.

632
00:36:35.902 --> 00:36:36.903
Let's do it.

633
00:36:49.749 --> 00:36:52.752
You ready. brother?
Just got word it's time to head up.

634
00:36:54.754 --> 00:36:55.796
You okay?

635
00:36:56.422 --> 00:36:58.382
- What. is your suit too tight?
- Ha!

636
00:36:59.467 --> 00:37:00.676
Nah. I just...

637
00:37:02.511 --> 00:37:05.765
I've been thinking about
what you and Mike said about

638
00:37:06.849 --> 00:37:08.851
the guy that Mel is marrying.

639
00:37:11.562 --> 00:37:12.855
You up for a little mission?

640
00:37:16.567 --> 00:37:19.153
Won't be much longer.
The ceremony's about to start. okay?

641
00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:21.656
What do you say
I get us some lemonade. huh?

642
00:37:21.739 --> 00:37:23.241
- Okay.
- All right. Be right back.

643
00:37:33.292 --> 00:37:34.293
Hey.

644
00:37:34.835 --> 00:37:36.128
- Hey.
- Uh...

645
00:37:36.921 --> 00:37:39.006
- Could I talk to you for a sec?
- Uh...

646
00:37:39.799 --> 00:37:40.800
Yeah. sure.

647
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:55.064
So. uh. what's up?

648
00:37:55.147 --> 00:37:57.984
What's up is you brought a con woman
to my brother's wedding.

649
00:37:58.067 --> 00:37:59.694
She's not a con woman. okay?

650
00:37:59.777 --> 00:38:04.323
She's... a woman who was committing a con.

651
00:38:04.407 --> 00:38:06.826
Oh. well. that is a very
subtle distinction. Brady.

652
00:38:06.909 --> 00:38:10.621
She made a mistake. okay?
She owned up to it. I forgave her.

653
00:38:10.705 --> 00:38:13.541
We moved on. Why do you care so much?

654
00:38:14.458 --> 00:38:18.546
I care because I care about you.
and you deserve better!

655
00:38:18.629 --> 00:38:19.839
Better than what?

656
00:38:20.381 --> 00:38:22.091
Lark's a good person.

657
00:38:22.174 --> 00:38:25.803
Who did what she thought she had to do
to take care of someone she loved.

658
00:38:26.595 --> 00:38:28.723
Maybe you don't understand that. but I do.

659
00:38:30.725 --> 00:38:31.725
Wow.

660
00:38:32.059 --> 00:38:33.644
- Okay.
- Look. hey. hey. hey.

661
00:38:35.438 --> 00:38:38.607
I didn't say that to hurt you. okay?
I didn't.

662
00:38:38.691 --> 00:38:40.985
Just me being with Lark is...

663
00:38:41.736 --> 00:38:43.571
It's not about you. Okay?

664
00:38:43.654 --> 00:38:46.198
It's about me.
Trying to get a fresh start.

665
00:38:46.282 --> 00:38:48.993
trying to move on. Like you did with Mike.

666
00:38:49.076 --> 00:38:51.329
- So why can't you just let me?
- I can.

667
00:38:51.954 --> 00:38:54.749
I just...
You know. I want more for you.

668
00:38:54.832 --> 00:38:58.794
I want you to be with a woman
who at least matches you.

669
00:38:58.878 --> 00:39:02.423
who challenges you.
who brings out the best in you.

670
00:39:02.506 --> 00:39:03.507
I was.

671
00:39:04.675 --> 00:39:05.676
I was.

672
00:39:06.469 --> 00:39:08.429
- But she didn't want me.
- Yes. she did.

673
00:39:14.435 --> 00:39:18.105
Being with you made me forget
what I had been through.

674
00:39:19.106 --> 00:39:21.650
But it always was such a mess. Brady.

675
00:39:23.611 --> 00:39:25.738
I got lost in you.
you know?

676
00:39:25.821 --> 00:39:28.407
- I was running away.
- Yeah. maybe. Maybe.

677
00:39:28.991 --> 00:39:31.035
Or maybe you fell in love with me.

678
00:39:32.203 --> 00:39:33.704
Obviously I did.

679
00:39:38.709 --> 00:39:40.294
Do you still love me?

680
00:39:45.633 --> 00:39:48.344
- A part of me will...
- Don't do that. Don't bullshit me.

681
00:39:49.762 --> 00:39:52.473
- Either you do or you don't. Which is it?
- I'm with Mike!

682
00:39:52.556 --> 00:39:54.433
And I'm with Lark. Do you love me?

683
00:39:57.853 --> 00:39:59.730
- Do you still love me?
- Yes!

684
00:40:00.481 --> 00:40:01.481
God!

685
00:40:01.857 --> 00:40:02.857
Yes!

686
00:40:03.442 --> 00:40:06.028
I've loved you since the moment I met you!

687
00:40:06.112 --> 00:40:09.198
I knew in the first ten seconds
that you were the one for me.

688
00:40:10.324 --> 00:40:11.742
That was never the question.

689
00:40:13.035 --> 00:40:15.204
The question was whether or not
I was the one for you.

690
00:40:16.789 --> 00:40:18.416
You were. but you messed it up.

691
00:40:18.499 --> 00:40:19.708
I did what I had to do!

692
00:40:19.792 --> 00:40:21.961
- You lied...
- To protect you!

693
00:40:22.878 --> 00:40:26.841
And I'm not gonna apologize for that.
Because if I had to do it all over again...

694
00:40:26.924 --> 00:40:30.052
If I had to lose you
just to keep you safe.

695
00:40:30.136 --> 00:40:31.679
I would do it in a heartbeat.

696
00:40:34.348 --> 00:40:36.809
Brie. I'd do anything for you.

697
00:40:37.435 --> 00:40:40.396
Anything at all. And you know what?
It's goddamn terrifying.

698
00:40:42.356 --> 00:40:44.316
'Cause I know I will never

699
00:40:45.276 --> 00:40:48.487
feel that way
about someone else ever again.

700
00:40:50.906 --> 00:40:51.906
No one.

701
00:41:28.944 --> 00:41:31.064
I can't believe you're getting married.

702
00:41:31.113 --> 00:41:33.532
- Again.
- Yeah. that makes two of us.

703
00:41:33.616 --> 00:41:36.660
I mean. it's not that I didn't love Mark.
Because I did.

704
00:41:36.744 --> 00:41:39.246
- I know.
- But this just feels different.

705
00:41:39.747 --> 00:41:42.708
Yeah. it is. It is different.

706
00:41:42.791 --> 00:41:44.543
- Yeah.
- You know? It's...

707
00:41:44.627 --> 00:41:46.462
It's still kind of surreal. though.

708
00:41:48.088 --> 00:41:52.468
Well. truly. this day is everything
I could have ever wished for you.

709
00:41:52.551 --> 00:41:53.551
Hmm.

710
00:42:00.976 --> 00:42:02.102
Hey. what's happening?

711
00:42:02.686 --> 00:42:03.729
Um...

712
00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:05.606
I don't know.

713
00:42:07.316 --> 00:42:08.400
What can I do?

714
00:42:09.610 --> 00:42:10.611
How can I help?

715
00:42:11.111 --> 00:42:13.155
Hey.

716
00:42:14.448 --> 00:42:15.991
I need you to do me a favor.

717
00:42:21.413 --> 00:42:23.374
- Hey.
- Your bride would like to see you.

718
00:42:51.318 --> 00:42:52.318
Hi.

719
00:42:53.904 --> 00:42:55.072
Hey. yourself.

720
00:42:59.868 --> 00:43:01.287
Wow! Um...

721
00:43:02.705 --> 00:43:04.123
I'm really glad we did this.

722
00:43:04.206 --> 00:43:06.709
'cause if I'd gotten
my first look at you at the altar.

723
00:43:06.792 --> 00:43:09.086
I don't think I'd remember my vows.

724
00:43:10.504 --> 00:43:11.797
It's just a dress.

725
00:43:13.090 --> 00:43:14.508
It's not the dress.

726
00:43:21.098 --> 00:43:22.098
How you feeling?

727
00:43:24.059 --> 00:43:25.060
I feel

728
00:43:26.312 --> 00:43:30.357
like the luckiest girl in the world
who is a million miles away.

729
00:43:32.359 --> 00:43:33.359
Okay.

730
00:43:33.902 --> 00:43:35.904
At first. I thought this was about my dad.

731
00:43:37.573 --> 00:43:38.741
but I think...

732
00:43:39.283 --> 00:43:40.993
I think it might be about

733
00:43:41.994 --> 00:43:43.621
trusting in forever again.

734
00:43:46.040 --> 00:43:49.209
Trusting that the people that I love
aren't gonna just disappear on me.

735
00:43:49.293 --> 00:43:51.587
I can't lose you. Jack.

736
00:43:54.131 --> 00:43:56.091
But I can't walk down the aisle

737
00:43:56.175 --> 00:43:59.011
with all of these ghosts
floating around in my head.

738
00:44:02.931 --> 00:44:03.974
Okay.

739
00:44:06.518 --> 00:44:07.936
Then let's get out of here.

740
00:44:11.440 --> 00:44:12.441
Come on.

741
00:44:14.568 --> 00:44:15.568
Let's go.

742
00:44:26.205 --> 00:44:27.623
- Hey.
- Hey.

743
00:44:28.415 --> 00:44:29.625
You okay?

744
00:44:29.708 --> 00:44:32.461
Yeah. yeah! No. I'm good.
It was just a thing.

745
00:44:33.379 --> 00:44:35.881
Lizzie. there you are.
I didn't get a chance to tell you

746
00:44:35.964 --> 00:44:37.549
